caption: Great restaurant glad they are still in area
Some of the best authentic Greek Cuisine I've tasted. Personally love the Souvlaki and Gyros the grape pie is unique and delicious !
Best Greek Food in town. The guy at the register (jimmy I believe, ugly dude) but very helpful. Highly recommend!!!!
chicken souvlaki pita 10/10 bean salad 10/10 very cute spot
Food was amazing!
The food is excellent. I enjoyed the lamb gyro, the greek salad, the potato salad and the buttermilk pie.
Good not great. To much vinegarette not enough feta on the Gyro
Great Gyro's!

So I meant to take a photo, but I ate all my food before I remembered to! I got a Lamb Gyro with Dolmades, and a friend got the Spinach Greek salad. Both were incredible! The lamb was delicious and there was plenty of tzatziki. The dolmades were equally as good! I will definitely come back here!
The best place ever I gotta go once a week for my well-being.
The service was very helpful and welcoming. The bill was fair. I see why this place has so many good reviews.

Food is lacking on flavor love that it's a family own business.The whole is healthy choice but and if you don't like potato salad in your Greek salad don't come here.been living here for six years won't go back
Great

Authentic falafel sandwiches served here... This isn’t your typical falafel served up at like those “fried chicken “ halal spots .. no.. completely different. You’re comparing North Pole to South Pole.  Try it and find out why
Love it food is super good and filling. Love all the healthy options. 👍🏻⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Amazing food.  Stopped here on a road trip. Great parking and outdoor seats with the dogs.
We have ordered from Despina many times and it is the best Greek food we've had ever! So fresh and flavorful.
Friendly staff and great greek
Amazing food and always made fresh!!  My favorites are the hummus, the Sophia, the spinach pie, their salads with the fun surprise of potato salad at the bottom and all of their soups are the best!!
Haven't been there in a minute. Went back today...I was in heaven! Mmmm
Lamb Gyro for the win
so yummy:)
Healthy food, fresh salad. Out of the ordinary menu
The people are so nice and food is always great
The best Greek food around! Always fresh and made by Despina!

Their new location is wonderful! My coworkers and I love grabbing lunch here. Some people may complain about the wait/ price but everything is fresh and made when you order it. It helps to order ahead if you’re in a rush. Whatever is on special is sure to be amazing.
Delicious food! I really enjoy coming here and eating. The only reason I won’t give it 5 stars is because Despina’s completely ruined my reputation...

The food was good. The gyro was a little small but good. The place has no ambiance. It's more of a take out joint. Parking is on the street and its metered. The service was good. It's a three star eatery.
Great atmosphere. Great family! Best Greek food on earth!

Despina's is an authentic Greek restaurant that serves the best homemade hummus, tabouli, gyros, baklava and buttermilk pie and much more! The food is to die for! Even more importantly, this restaurant's level of service to the Binghamton community is outstanding. The owner, Despina and her family strive to treat everyone like family!
Hmmm always a delious lunch place! Never disappoints!
Ok

I'm so glad we chose Despina's for our lunch! I had the "make your own platter" with tzatziki, hummus, tabouli, lamb gyro meat, and pita. My son had chicken souvlaki and tabouli. Everything was perfectly seasoned and absolutely delicious! The cafe itself is very cute. The gentleman at the counter was helpful and accommodating. The only downside was the roadwork that was going on right outside the cafe. I will definitely be coming back to try more off the menu!
really good food; really awesome environment  definitely will be back; what an awesome find
A family Mediterranean restaurant with great food and excellent customer service.
Amazing homemade foods, great and personable consumer service. Would 100% recommend it to anyone. The salads and gyros were phenomenal, definitely coming back with friends.
Absolutely amazing, authentic Greek. Super sweet staff and generous! If you want a taste of the Mediterranean, stop by!!

Great upbeat Sunny atmosphere it's a seat yourself after order at the counter Greek food that is fantastic. Corner seating for large groups. great for lunch you can spend between $7 and $10 and get a lot of food! Their hummus is perfect!
Great food will go back again.

Very wonderful decor and atmosphere! The food seems to be made with love, which is suitable but rarely found even in family restaurants such as these. The owner is clearly proud of her quality food, quality service, and you can occasionally overhear the pride and love she has for her grandchildren who work there as well. This is personally my favorite aspect as it almost makes you feel like being at your own grandma's house.

I love this place! Excellent, counter service, food. Great, friendly service. A very nice design inside. Not sure what they do to the pita bread before serving but I've had about 7 gyros here and each time the pita has been better than any I've ever had elsewhere! A bit on the pricey side. Gyro and a Greek salad (with add-on potato salad burried under salad) including tax is $13 (even with no drink); and that is a "special". The only non-wonderful thing about this place is that they supply music to the large room from the default speaker in a single tv. Not terrible; just not in keeping with how classy EVERYTHING else about this place is. Remote speakers would go a long way.
Lamb Gryo was delicious! I will definitely be coming back

Really welcoming and friendly restaurant. The staff are really nice and they help you to find something really good to eat if you're not familiar with Mediterranean food. I've been here a few times and went out on a limb trying some things that were new and really enjoyed them. It's not the most inexpensive place to eat but it's hard to find Mediterranean food in the area and I feel like this is a really good balance between quality and price. You can grab a quick gyro and a drink and go for a walk down Washington Street to explore downtown a little bit, it's pretty nice on a warmer day.
Excellent food at a family-owned business

This place is family owned with a welcoming freindly atmosphere and great food.  The pita bread is so light an flavorful.  I have had the lamb ylgyro and beef souvlaki, both were super.  The tabouli is fantastic as are the grape leaves.  This is a must visit 8f you are in downtown Binghamton.

Pricy, small portions, everything I ordered seemed to come out of a precooked package as opposed to being made there. Gyro meat was being warmed on a George Foreman type griddle. It tasted fine.   But I would consider this one of the less authentic Greek establishments.

Family feel restaurant where almost everything is home made. House salad dressing is incredible. Spanakopita was the best I’ve ever had. They have a homemade beef mixture to place in their Euro and paired with the air baked fries was a home run. To top it all off at the end of diner they brought out a free whoopie pie for our table. We bought 3 more because they were amazing! Great experience and wonderful pricing.
A beautiful space with tasty food.

Good food friendly staff. Had the gyro and fries everything was hot and tasted great. Had some baklava for dessert was very good and the lady working the front was very helpful and friendly was a nice place will go back again.
Food was quite good, but we waited for 35 - 45 minutes for our meal. Not sure why as the place wasn't too busy.

Delicious food. Authentic. Grape leaves done so well, tortellini soup is amazing, greek salad is delicious. Only thing I'm not 100% on is the lettuce in the salad being shredded iceberg. Gets soggy and sort of stringy with dressing.
My go to place when I want a salad. Best falafel I've ever had also!

One of my go to places for clean and healthy food in Binghamton. The portion of the food and quality of the food had always been 5/5. Also try Despina’s dessert options, she makes exceptional baklava , pies and other Greek desserts. They have a very friendly staff and totally run by family. They also have good number of vegan and vegetarian option.
Fablous food.
Great good, great people, authentic Greek food.  A place I need to visit more often.
Very elegant atmosphere. Great staff.
Very tasty Greek food, reasonable prices.
Good Gyros
Been going for years. Chicken souvlaki and potato salad is on point. Despina is very friendly and her desserts, especially the baklava are fantastic.

Some of the best Mediterranean food I've had. Staff was always very nice. Just very disappointed that they no longer have Saturday hours since I live out of town and would come in on the weekends to eat here.
Great food best soup in town

This place is great! I hated Greek food until I discovered this place, they totally reversed my opinion on Greek food. The burgers is delicious. And the customer service is phenomenal. I definitely give this place 2 thumbs up. I can’t think of one bad thing to say about this place even if I tried. Literally everything on the menu taste fantastic!
Pricey for what it is.
Phenomenal Greek food, excellent service.  Extremely friendly staff!
Great food!  Convenient downtown location
Great food!
Good food, clean restaurant, I would recommend it. Ate the falafel sandwich, turkey panini, and tiramisu.
Great, homemade food! Friendly service. Always delicious.
Lovely restaurant and great food!
Food was really good...Service was good also!
Great Greek food! Friendly staff.
Stopped here for lunch on a road trip through the area. The food was delicious and a really great value. Clean restaurant, amazing food, friendly staff!!! If I lived closer I'd eat here every week!!
Absolutely amazing food and excellent service
This is one of the best Binghamton restaurant. And it's on the cheeper side. I recommend this place i go there all the time for coffee and use the free WiFi
The most delicious greek cuisine that I have ever had, quaint atmosphere, and great service
Great falafel and quick service!
Authentic Greek food!  The owner is very kind. The food is absolutely delicious!

I love Despina's!  Despina's is my number 1 go to restaurant! Their authentic homemade Greek food is some of the best I have ever tasted.  Their food and service always EXCEEDS my expectations.  Go try Despina's, you will not be disappointed!
Some of the best food in town. If you have a chance, step out the box and visit Despina's - one of the top five restaurants in Binghamton N.Y in my eyes Despina's.

My God, what a find! Homemade, Greek food from scratch! My husband had the Sophia and I had the falafel pita. The falafel was absolutely perfect and the tzatiki was amazing. And the Sophia was a great twist on classic Greek flavors... can't decide which meal was more delicious. I would pay twice as much for food like this. We live in Colorado... but we will come here every time we pass thru Binghamton. Thanks for all the love you so obviously put into your food!
Great food, and excellent customer service. No other food in this area like it!
Great lunch spot. Tasty Greek food, courteous service, comfortable atmosphere. Great vegan options, I love the falafel with hummus and 3 bean salad!
Great family atmosphere! We take our daughter at least once a week and she loves Elpi and Jimmy! I would recommend this restaurant to anybody!
Probably the best, homemade Greek food I've ever eaten. The restaurant itself is spartan and not very comfy, so I recommend take-out.
Excellent
Best. Potato. Salad. Ever.
Amazing! I've followed her from two different locations. My favorite restaurant!!

Went in for the first time with my best friend, and we both were amazed by the options they had on the menu. They had awesome drinks (juices, coffee, iced coffees), and the chicken Caesar pita was amazing! The potato salad was fresh and delicious as well. I'll definitely be going back again!
Best salads and best paninis in downtown Binghamton.  Service is great too.  Check it out!

I went with my fiancee after a walk. We ordered two pita sandwiches-- one falafel and one lamb gyro-- and two drinks, for under $10. We were pleasantly surprised by great pita, great sides, and excellent falafel and lamb. The setting isn't bad either!
Very good gyro. Mediocre iced coffee though.
Great food. She has amazing vegan options all the food is cooked to order. You won't be disappointed.
